==>  Describe the roles of the client and server in web communication.  Network Layers on Client and Server


Client (Frontend Side)

A client is the device or application that requests data.

Server (Backend Side)

A server is a system that receives requests and sends responses.


Network Layers on Client and Server

Communication follows a layered model called the OSI Model.

** OSI Model (7 Layers)

Physical

Data Link

Network

Transport

Session

Presentation

Application

